process.on('uncaughtException',  (err) => { console.error(err); process.exit(1); });
```

## 3. Input validation is not wired up

Neither route currently takes user input, but the moment you add query/body/param handling (e.g. `/users/:id`), you'll need validation. Establish the pattern now:

