`/users` currently returns emails. In a real system, emails are PII — return them only to authenticated callers and consider field-level authorization.

### 6. Disable the `X-Powered-By` header
`helmet()` does this, but if you don't use helmet: `app.disable('x-powered-by');` — avoids advertising Express to attackers.

### 7. Handle `listen` errors
```js
const server = app.listen(PORT)
  .on('error', (err) => { console.error('Listen failed', err); process.exit(1); });
```

### 8. Graceful shutdown
