The file is small and straightforward, but even simple Express apps have rough edges worth tightening before they ship. Here are concrete suggestions organized by priority.

## 1. Missing global error handling

The app has no error-handling middleware, so any thrown error or rejected promise in a handler will either crash the process or leak a stack trace to the client.

**Add an error handler at the bottom of the middleware stack:**
```js
